138. 21. Sibyllae interpretes, iu. the quindecimviri sacris faciun- dis, a college of which the duty was to keep the Sibylline books, to consult them on the order of the Senate, to report thereon and to carry out the necessary religious observances prescribed by them3 from which last duty the title of the office was taken. They were called quindecimviri since the year 673 (probably) ; before this decemviri, since 3785 in the earlier period duoviri.
